# 2. 最高のプラン

Shiho: (I'm glad I got off work early today.)
Shiho: (Now I can go home and listen to the new CD I just bought.)
Shiho: (Then I'll practice until it's time for dinner, and...)
Shiho: Huh...?
Shiho: Doesn't Saki work over at that cafe?
Shiho: (And I'm seeing some familiar faces in the window...)
Shiho: Huh...?
Shiho: What are those three doing there together?
Shiho: (From what I can see, they're not studying together or anything. They have a bunch of books and magazines laid out on their table...)
Shiho: (I don't know what's going on, but if they see me, it's going to be a whole thing. I'll just pass by quickly...)
Shiho: Oh...
Shiho: (They saw me.)
Shiho: So, what are you guys doing with all these books and magazines?
Tsukasa: Oh, I'm glad you asked!
Tsukasa: We were just in the middle of planning the Tenma-Hinomori Leaf-Viewing Reattempt!
Shiho: Reattempt? Oh, you mean our day trip.
Shizuku: Yes, Saki said she could join in after her shift ended and asked us to meet here...
Shizuku: So, the three of us have decided to plan our trip together.
Shiho: I see...
Shiho: By the way, what do you guys have in mind at the moment?
Saki: We're still brainstorming, but here are our notes!
Shiho: Let's see...
Shiho: “Leaf-viewing followed by river rafting, lunch and a foot bath. Visit the art museum, have tea at a trendy cafe, visit the local shrine, climb a mountain and go fruit picking.”
Shizuku: Doesn't it all sound like so much fun?
Shiho: Yeah, but... It's not going to be possible to do all these things in one day. Each of these places are pretty far apart, too, so that's gonna be a lot of time spent in transit...
Tsukasa: Yes, I had a feeling... I was hoping that we could fit in a few extra activities with efficient enough routing.
Saki: Haha. We sorta couldn't help ourselves. We just kept finding all these great things to do...
Saki: Just take this magazine, for instance. It gives all these recommendations and goes into so much detail.
Saki: Wait, Tsukasa, check this out! The rope bridge on this map looks really fun! It apparently creaks and wobbles like crazy!
Tsukasa: Oh, look at that! And based on its height, it likely offers a spectacular view.
Shizuku: Then, let's add it to the list.
Shiho: (This is bad. If I let these three handle everything, they won't have anything decided by the day of...)
Shiho: (I have no choice.)
Shiho: If you guys just keep adding to that list, then you're not gonna get anything done.
Shiho: You won't be able to come up with a real plan if you keep cramming in more and more activities.
Tsukasa: Urgh... Fair point...!
Shiho: You already have plenty on this list, so it's time to start narrowing down which are our most viable options.
Shiho: Why don't we begin by coming up with the goal for this trip?
Shizuku: The goal...?
Shiho: Our primary goal is to see the leaves, right? So, we should begin by picking where we're going to do that.
Shiho: Then, we can start looking at other places to visit and activities to do. Wouldn't that help smooth out this process?
Tsukasa: Yes, that's excellent...!
Saki: Oh, then... How about we go leaf-viewing on this mountain?
Saki: Look! It even says that now's the best time to see them!
Shizuku: Yes, and it's close enough that we can travel there and back by train.
Tsukasa: Oh, there's even a historical village nearby with old buildings and cafes, as well as a vineyard where we can pick our own grapes!
Tsukasa: Fall is all about bountiful harvests! We must take this opportunity to go fruit picking, no?
Shiho: A historical village and fruit picking...
Shiho: We can visit both using a bus. Why don't we add them to the list?
Saki: Whoa...! Our itinerary's coming together so fast!
Shizuku: Thank you for doing this, Shii. We really appreciate it.
Tsukasa: Alright, let's use this momentum to keep hammering out the details of our trip!
Saki & Shizuku: Yeah!
Tsukasa: Okay! Does this itinerary look good to you?
Shiho: Yes, let's just check over our route one last time.
Shiho: After arriving at the station, we'll explore the historical village. We'll take a quick break at this cafe and then go fruit picking.
Shiho: Finally, we'll go leaf-viewing.
Saki: Wow...! We'll really get to do all the things we wanted in one day!
Saki: I'm excited to the max about this trip right now!
Tsukasa: Yes, I'm looking forward to this trip as well! I know! Why don't we practice picking grapes at home?!
Shiho: Wait, practice picking grapes...?
Shizuku: Thank you again, Shii. Thanks to you, I think we're in for a very fun trip now.
Shiho: It's fine. Honestly, I was worried about what would happen if I left you three to your own devices...
Shiho: (Despite them saying that they'd take care of all the planning, I ended up doing most of the work.)
Shiho: (Still...)
Shiho: (I can live with that.)
Shiho: (It's not often that we get to take trips like this together, so I should try to enjoy myself when we go.)
